<br>
<br>
<DIV class="poemtitle">Travelling</DIV><br>
<TABLE><TR><TD>
<br>Sorry, my friend, that I have not written<br />

sooner, but I have been travelling, far,<br />

over scored glacial plains where the bitten<br />

thornwood crouches beneath the north star;<br />

then farther, to where the seas roll like cold tar.<br />

I sailed that congealing, snow-crusted sea<br />

till it set hard and ice snapped my boat's spar.<br />

So cold it was, not a tear could flow free,<br />

and none trudged that frozen desert but me.<br />

When night condensed from the twilight gloom<br />

I stumbled, numbly, unable to see,<br />

my ice-thistled coat as hard as a tomb.<br />

But morning has brought a fall of rain<br />

thawing my hands, so I write again.<br />
<br />
<br>
<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('allinson')">by Mark Allinson</a>
</td></tr></table>
<br><br>
<br>
  <img src="images/allinson.jpg"><br>
